    "subtopics": [
      {
        "subtopic": "Green Hydrogen Certification Scheme (GHCI) & National Green Hydrogen Mission (NGHM)",
        "content": "The Ministry of New and Renewable Energy (MNRE) organized a National Workshop on “Opportunities for MSMEs in the Green Hydrogen Supply Chain” in New Delhi. Union Minister Pralhad Joshi launched the Green Hydrogen Certification Scheme of India (GHCI). The GHCI aims to **certify green hydrogen production in India** and ensure transparency, traceability, and market credibility. This scheme supports India’s **National Green Hydrogen Mission (NGHM)** and aims to establish India as a global hub for green hydrogen."
