    "topic": "2. Draft Greenhouse Gases Target Rules",
    "subtopics": [
      {
        "subtopic": "Draft Gases Emissions Intensity (GEI) Target Rules & Carbon Credit Trading Scheme (CCTS)",
        "content": "The Ministry of Environment, Forest and Climate Change (MoEFCC) notified the Draft Gases Emissions Intensity (GEI) Target Rules, 2025. These rules aim to implement the **Carbon Credit Trading Scheme (CCTS), 2023**. This supports India’s commitment under the Paris Agreement to reduce **GHG emissions intensity of GDP by 45% by 2030** compared to 2005 levels. GEI is measured in tonnes of CO₂ equivalent (tCO₂e) and covers major greenhouse gases including CO₂, CH₄, N₂O, CFCs, and HCFCs."
      }
    ]
  },
