    "topic": "13. ITER Fusion Project Milestone",
    "subtopics": [
      {
        "subtopic": "Contribution to ITER Fusion Project",
        "content": "India has emerged as a major contributor to a key breakthrough in the **ITER project**—the world’s most ambitious nuclear fusion initiative—by supplying the massive cryostat and related technologies [4]. India supplied the 30 m cryostat chamber, cryolines, in-wall shielding, cooling and heating systems that create the Tokamak’s ultra-cold, superconducting environment [4]. The sixth module of the Central Solenoid, ITER’s core magnet system, has been completed, providing sufficient magnetic force to confine plasma at 150 million °C [4]."
      }
    ]
  },
