    "topic": "37. Maternal Mortality Ratio Declines",
    "subtopics": [
      {
        "subtopic": "Decline in Maternal Mortality Ratio (MMR)",
        "content": "India has made significant progress in improving maternal health, with the **Maternal Mortality Ratio (MMR) declining to 93 per 1 lakh live births** during 2019-21, down from 97 in 2018-20 and 103 in 2017-19 [11]. This decline reflects the combined efforts of government policies, healthcare improvements, and increased awareness of maternal health services [11]. The MMR is a key indicator of a country’s reproductive health, calculated as the number of maternal deaths per 100,000 live births in a given period [11]."
      }
    ]
