    "topic": "38. GeM 8th Anniversary Celebrated",
    "subtopics": [
      {
        "subtopic": "Government e-Marketplace (GeM) Achievements",
        "content": "The **Government e-Marketplace (GeM)**, India’s digital public procurement portal, celebrated its **8th Incorporation Day on May 19, 2025** [12]. Launched in 2016, GeM has played a pivotal role in transforming government procurement by making it more inclusive, transparent, and efficient [12]. Over **10 lakh Micro and Small Enterprises (MSEs)**, 1.84 lakh women entrepreneurs, and 1.3 lakh artisans and weavers have been onboarded [12]. GeM also launched **GeMAI, India’s first Generative AI-powered chatbot** for public sector services, supporting voice and text in 10 Indian languages [13]. GeM is now adopted by all 36 States/UTs, with mandatory usage in 8 states including Gujarat, Maharashtra, and Assam [13]."
