    "subtopics": [
      {
        "subtopic": "Commemorative Postage Stamp for Kodaikanal Solar Observatory",
        "content": "The Department of Posts released a **commemorative postage stamp to mark 125 years of the Kodaikanal Solar Observatory** [15]. The stamp showcases the observatory’s twin-domed building, which houses a 6-inch telescope (from 1850) and an 8-inch telescope (from 1866) [16]. It also includes a recent H-alpha solar image and a Butterfly Diagram showing sunspot positions [16]. The Kodaikanal Solar Observatory was established on April 1, 1899, in Tamil Nadu and is affiliated with the Indian Institute of Astrophysics (IIA) [17]."
