    "subtopics": [
      {
        "subtopic": "Sagar Mein Samman (SMS) Initiative",
        "content": "Union Minister Shri Sarbananda Sonowal unveiled the **Sagar Mein Samman (SMS) initiative** on International Day for Women in Maritime in Mumbai [19]. This initiative aims to build a future-ready, **gender-equitable maritime workforce** by boosting women’s participation across all seafaring and shore-based roles [19]. It includes a **100% Subsidy Scheme** and aligns with the government’s DEI objectives under Maritime India Vision 2030 [20]. Empowerment targets include **12% female representation in technical maritime roles by 2030**, with a recorded **739 percent rise in registered women seafarers** from 1,699 (2015) to 14,255 (2024) [20]."
