    "topic": "43. Article 143 Invoked on Governor Powers",
    "subtopics": [
      {
        "subtopic": "Supreme Court’s Advisory Opinion on Governor’s Assent Powers",
        "content": "President Droupadi Murmu invoked **Article 143 of the Indian Constitution to seek the Supreme Court’s advisory opinion** [21]. This move was triggered by an April 8, 2025, Supreme Court judgment which held the Tamil Nadu Governor’s delay in assenting to Bills as unconstitutional [21]. The President referred **14 key constitutional questions** concerning the powers of Governors and the President in dealing with State legislation under Articles 200 and 201 [22]. The Supreme Court, invoking Article 142, had declared the Governor’s inaction illegal and deemed that the Bills had received assent [22]."
