    "topic": "50. IRFC Deep-Discount Bonds Approved",
    "subtopics": [
      {
        "subtopic": "IRFC Deep-Discount Bonds",
        "content": "Indian Railway Finance Corporation (IRFC) has received government approval to raise **$1.17 billion through deep-discount bonds** [33]. Deep-discount bonds are issued at a discount to face value and do not pay regular interest [33]. IRFC’s board approved raising **₹60,000 crore in FY26** to support its capital needs, shifting focus beyond railways to sectors with forward and backward linkages such as ports, renewables, and tourism [34]. Other PSUs like HUDCO and PFC have also been allowed to raise deep-discount bonds [34]. IRFC was founded on December 12, 1986, with headquarters in New Delhi [35]."
