    "topic": "52. DAP Prices Surge Fertiliser Subsidy Impact",
    "subtopics": [
      {
        "subtopic": "DAP Price Increase and Impact on Fertiliser Subsidy",
        "content": "The global price of **di-ammonium phosphate (DAP) has risen over 13% since April**, currently at $652/tonne [37]. DAP is the second most consumed fertilizer in India after urea [37]. India meets its DAP demand mainly through imports, so the price rise increases import costs for companies [37]. Retail prices of phosphatic and potassic (P&K) fertilisers were decontrolled in 2010 with the introduction of a fixed subsidy regime under the Nutrient Based Subsidy (NBS) mechanism [38]."
      }
    ]
